Connect FilterBar and FilterDrawer to the search API.

## Dependencies
- dogpile-bh5.4 (API search endpoint)
- dogpile-qdr.3 (FilterBar component)
- dogpile-qdr.4 (FilterDrawer component)

## State Management

### Filter Store
Create a SolidJS store for filter state:
```typescript
// apps/web/src/stores/filterStore.ts
import { createStore } from 'solid-js/store'

export const [filters, setFilters] = createStore({
  query: '',
  size: null as string | null,
  ageGroup: null as string | null,
  city: null as string | null,
  sex: null as string | null,
  goodWithKids: null as boolean | null,
  goodWithDogs: null as boolean | null,
  goodWithCats: null as boolean | null,
})

export const clearFilters = () => setFilters({
  query: '', size: null, ageGroup: null, city: null,
  sex: null, goodWithKids: null, goodWithDogs: null, goodWithCats: null
})
```

### API Integration
```typescript
// apps/web/src/api/dogs.ts
export async function searchDogs(filters: Filters): Promise<Dog[]> {
  const params = new URLSearchParams()
  if (filters.query) params.set('q', filters.query)
  if (filters.size) params.set('size', filters.size)
  if (filters.ageGroup) params.set('age', filters.ageGroup)
  if (filters.city) params.set('city', filters.city)

  const res = await fetch(`${API_URL}/dogs/search?${params}`)
  const data = await res.json()
  return data.dogs
}
```

### Reactive Search
```typescript
// In DogGrid.tsx
const [dogs] = createResource(
  () => filters,  // Track filter changes
  searchDogs,
  { initialValue: [] }
)
```

## Debouncing
- Query input: 300ms debounce
- Chip/filter clicks: immediate

## URL State
- Sync filters to URL params for shareability
- On page load, read filters from URL

## Testing
- Type in search, verify API called after 300ms
- Click chip, verify immediate filter
- Share URL with filters, verify persisted

Create compact, emotional hero with scrapbook/polaroid design.

## Location
`apps/web/src/components/Hero.astro`

## Design Specs

### Layout
- Height: 60-70vh max (shows search bar above fold)
- Background: Curved/convex bottom edge pointing to content

### Polaroid Collage
- Desktop: 3 overlapping polaroid frames with dog photos
- Mobile: Single stacked pile, top photo tilts on scroll
- 'Taped' effect on corners (CSS pseudo-elements like washi tape)
- Slight rotation on each frame (-3deg, 2deg, -1deg)

### Copy (Polish)
```
Headline: "Twój nowy najlepszy przyjaciel już tu czeka."
Subheadline: "Psy z całego kraju w jednym miejscu. Znajdź tego jedynego."
```

### Trust Signal
- Ticker: "12 psów znalazło dom dzisiaj" (animated count)

## CSS Classes Needed
```css
.polaroid {
  background: white;
  padding: 1rem 1rem 3rem;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  transform: rotate(var(--rotation));
}

.tape-effect::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  /* washi tape styling */
}

.hero-curve {
  clip-path: ellipse(150% 100% at 50% 0%);
}
```

## Animations
- Subtle Ken Burns drift on photos (slow zoom/pan)
- Polaroids slightly shift on scroll (parallax)

## Mobile
- Stack polaroids vertically with overlap
- Reduce text size
- Ensure CTA visible above fold

Build the main search/filter bar with sticky behavior and quick chips.

## Location
`apps/web/src/components/FilterBar.tsx` (SolidJS for interactivity)

## Design Specs

### Appearance
- Floating pill shape with rounded corners
- Glassmorphism: translucent white + backdrop-blur(8px)
- Subtle shadow for depth
- Overlaps hero bottom initially (negative margin)

### Sticky Behavior
- Normal position: overlapping hero bottom
- On scroll past hero: sticks to top (position: sticky)
- Smooth transition, no jarring jump

### Content
1. **Search Input** - left side, icon + placeholder
2. **Quick Chips** - horizontal scroll on mobile
   - Szczeniaki (Puppies)
   - Małe (Small)
   - Średnie (Medium)
   - Duże (Large)
   - Seniorzy (Seniors)
3. **Filter Button** - right side, opens bottom sheet

### Mobile Layout
```
[🔍 Szukaj...        ] [⚙️]
[Szczeniaki][Małe][Średnie][Duże]...
```
- Chips horizontally scrollable
- Filter button opens drawer

### Desktop Layout
```
[🔍 Szukaj psa...] [Szczeniaki][Małe][Średnie][Duże][Seniorzy] [Więcej filtrów]
```

## State Management
- Selected chips highlighted
- Search input debounced (300ms)
- Emit filter changes to parent/store

## CSS
```css
.filter-bar {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
  backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  border-radius: 9999px;
  position: sticky;
  top: 1rem;
  z-index: 40;
}

.chip {
  @apply px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-medium;
  @apply bg-white/50 hover:bg-white transition;
}

.chip.active {
  @apply bg-sys-nature-clay text-white;
}
```

Add scroll-triggered staggered fade-up animation for dog cards.

## Location
`apps/web/src/components/DogGrid.tsx`

## Animation Spec
- Cards start: opacity-0, translateY(16px)
- Cards end: opacity-100, translateY(0)
- Stagger: 50ms delay per card in viewport batch
- Trigger: when card enters viewport (IntersectionObserver)

## Implementation Options

### Option A: CSS + IntersectionObserver
```tsx
// In DogGrid.tsx
import { onMount, For, createSignal } from 'solid-js'

export default function DogGrid(props) {
  let gridRef: HTMLDivElement

  onMount(() => {
    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
      (entries) => {
        entries.forEach((entry, i) => {
          if (entry.isIntersecting) {
            const card = entry.target as HTMLElement
            card.style.transitionDelay = `${i * 50}ms`
            card.classList.add('revealed')
            observer.unobserve(card)
          }
        })
      },
      { threshold: 0.1 }
    )

    gridRef.querySelectorAll('.dog-card').forEach(card => {
      observer.observe(card)
    })
  })

  return (
    <div ref={gridRef} class="grid ...">
      <For each={dogs()}>
        {(dog) => <DogCard class="dog-card opacity-0 translate-y-4" dog={dog} />}
      </For>
    </div>
  )
}
```

### CSS
```css
.dog-card {
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateY(16px);
  transition: opacity 400ms ease-out, transform 400ms ease-out;
}

.dog-card.revealed {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateY(0);
}
```

### Option B: Use motion library (if needed)
- solid-motionone or similar
- More control, but adds bundle size

## Considerations
- Don't animate on initial page load if cards visible
- Reset animation on filter change (new results)
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion

## Testing
- Scroll down slowly, see cards fade up sequentially
- Filter, new cards animate in
- Check performance on mobile (no jank)

